<li>Which is the graph of \(f(x)\)? Select the correct graph.</li></ol>

[[input:ans6]] [[validation:ans6]][[feedback:prt6]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>It is enough to substitute the value of \(x\) given and then compute the absolute value. Consider, i.e., \(x=-3\), then we have \(f(x)=|x-2|=|-3-2|=|-5|=5\). Now consider \(x=-2\), then \(f(x)=|-2-2|=|-4|=4\). You can proceed in this way for all the other values of \(x\).</li>
<li>You can sketch the graph of the function using the points found in the table. You can draw those points and then join them by lines.</li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
